d before I went to school, just - brought it out like that. He looked - I can see him now. Take those clothes off - he said - take those clothes off and strip. Out that sink, scrubbing brush, scrubbed me and - me, I was all naked from this upwards and as 
I
 - turned on the tap and he scrubbed me down - skin off my back, I'll teach you to be clean. My mother cried. She could have gone to court, it was said, that was when we was young. That's the sort of father's living in them days, I expect there's some abo
u
t now but - and yet I say as I told you - he could be human. It's a freak - and when he was drunk he used to have a - he; was wounded in the head and on the arms with spears. The funny thing about it is it come up to a bump like that. One here - one here.
 When he got drunk up come them here - so I ignore - affect - that may have affected him.
