e respect - they made you respect - my father made you - and so did mother, make you respect anybody older than yourself. Oh yes. Was taught that way. I think that was good too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Yes. You had - you had to respect one another, not - not as seniors, but as your brothers - and sisters, yes, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did they say you should hit back or not it another child hurt you?
