Well the - they had - afterwards they got the - the undertaker you got to ask for what you want - this frame. Well we already had one of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 They didn't wear any special clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Yes, we used to go round to a friend of my mothers I know - that's what the enjoyment we had, mentioning that. They used to have a
 cup of tea with them every Saturday night and be there coming on main shopping street, up the side there. Used to be there at nights you know. Sometimes they'd see one or two but - I forgot all about that, good job you mentioned that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Your mother would take you there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Mother used to take us there and then - these children, their father was a bricklayer, see, and a teetotaler of sorts and living nicely. And - we're there, all gone and it was really be comfortably and all the comics there was rea
d 'em right through. It was a - thing to look forward to Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well - can't say I was because there was - honestly I - I can't remember - any shop for - only - we weren't the only - well we were - there's a lot like us, there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12075973\charrsid9580092 hundred}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  like us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes, I have done. I can't say what we done or what it was for like it's - that's - 'cos as I say he was a mostly a soldier and he went off to do this labouri
ng and then he was always busy, the only time we - as I can remember going off with him or following him was when we were trying to get his money off of him, on pension days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, Bank Holidays for example?
