We - we went - I remember once at school - when we were going to school, there was a Mrs Smith the next door neighbours and they came with - they knew somebody worked Huntley and Palmers. Huntley and Palmers had an annual outing by train to somew
here and I - and he'd probably got paid for that Saturday and it was a very cheap affair or something, it was three and six for adults and cheaper for children. They got the money, we went there because I can always remember it, I had threepence to spend 
on a - an outing at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 Hastings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 . Went with Huntley and Palmers to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12075973\charrsid9580092 
Hastings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 on a - to the seaside. And I always remember I brought back a penny - a little mirror with some shells round for a penny. It's as if it was up there now, I can see that penny mirror, I 
bought it home for my mother out of that threepence. We had - the sister next door she - had - we had boiled eggs. Had boiled eggs to eat in the train. Oh that's her - no it isn't my daughter, that's my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 niece}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 . 'Cos I - I always remember I looked at these b
oiled eggs 'cos they're blacky coloured see being boiled and everything else, and - I - I didn't want to eat 'em. She says, all right, we ate them you see. That's only the ones I can remember going to. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 Because it was very, very cheap, three and six return there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Huntley and Palmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Your parents didn't go on this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, no, no. They didn't. I think he went twice these children - as us children like you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever go away for a holiday up 'til 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did any of the family go?
