No, not - not - I can't - I can't think of any one of us going on a - having a holiday. Never at all. We used to go out - have - only the things we used to have in the old church meetings you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 And that's another thing, we used to go - see the
 church we used to attend was St Georges church, Brown up there, the coal merchants, he used to brush his carts out, his - his coal carts, they were horse and coats, brush the - the - brush them out, that's all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Then we used to go from St - from St Georges
 Road to St Georges Vicarage which is one, two, three roads along. Just by cart. That was the school treat. The Vicarage was about from here you might say up the - if you went up here and along the next road, the Vicarage was that far away from the - the 
church, and they were riding in an old coal cart. In a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 coal cart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 coal cart}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 . That had been swept out. Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 That was the church outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 
Yes, they used to grumble and row a bit because - the Methodist church along farther, and they used to go along there and up just up on to there on what they used to call Beachy Mill, up Tyler\rquote s there a bit farther. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And not only that they had it in a field, not in a Vicarage. Oh that was marvelous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh well I - before - when I - what you call it on the milk round, well all I done was - seemed to be indoors, nothing else to do. Whereas if - there was always a job of keeping them knives and forks clean with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 brick dust}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well church. Three times a day. Oh - you could - at night time you could go to any, we could go to St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 George\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  church or chapel or Salvation Army, as long as you went. But they used to check up on the old hymns regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you have any different clothes on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Nothing much. There might be a - sometimes we had a stiff collar - real stiff big collar you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Not - my father did see for a - every so often he was when he
 was in those - those moods as I said before, he was in those moods he'd go and - to the - a Baptist church that was he went to and we was all like St Georges church which is just that difference isn't it. Them two churches like, the Baptist. He'd go for 
s
ix months and be a regular and good attendants and get new recruits then he - started the old drinking again. See, that's what he'd do. But we were - all - all the family of us were - had - had to go to - as - as children we had to attend church. Sunday n
ights we could go to any place of worship like Sally Army, Methodist or anything. But we until had to go. My - my two elder brothers, because they were in the choir, they went to the St }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 George
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your mother go as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Mother wouldn't go very often. I couldn't tell you what she done before like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go to a Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. That's why I - I put it like. Three times - we had to go three times every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Yes. I - I told you that last week. Yes. Yes. About - well, say what - two or three hundred yards you might say or something like that. In the coal cart. That was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What other social activities organized by the church or chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
There wasn't any organized I - not to say like that. I - I played - like if I had a time off from the milk round and play a bit of football something like that, but there was - but they - they never had no - there was no - like Church Lads Brigade or a
nything like that. Not like - not our church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And you told me about the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How you get a good hiding for not going good enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes, I had a good hiding. I failed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Not
 our church, no, no. No, I belonged - my - when my father went to the Baptist church, the Baptist chapel and the Pleasant Sunday afternoons, he joined the I.T.T., Independent Order of Good Templars, see. That was held at - up - behind some lady's house or
 
- or a hall behind it, and I joined that like see, 'cos he made us join. And also - I - if it's not going off of it, when I was - when I joined the Army, see I - I went up in 1914 as a lad as I told you, my father come home, come out with us three sons, w
e
 was all home one weekend together, took us out, he never - we all went - went out to a pub out in - oh - over Burfield way, and he never said to me, have a drink of bear. It was - lemonade. He never forced it on me. I - I've got to hand that to him. See,
 he never tempted me, I was teetotaller and he never tempted me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever belong to any other club organized by the church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. There wasn't one, no, they never had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Well we had to say it before and after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Wed all say it together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Wasn't taught to but - mother asked us to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes, yes, he was a Liberal. He - he was that mad on that - on politics all that that when Rufus Issel got in he - he had a little - a - a small cannon and he filled it up with gunpowder and he - up the top of the ro
ad and he let it off bang and broke windows. A little - a little cannon, only a small - like the shape of a cannon, he filled that with gunpowder and he let it off, he was politically mad. Liberal. Yes, Sir Rufus Issels, he - he was Rufus Isaacs then. And
 
he - he was then envoy - a Viceroy of India wasn't he. And his son Gerald come on afterwards. Yes. He was M.P. for Reading. He lived at Wymax Park on the outlying parts. 'Cos my trouble with that, I went one of the - as a youngster, I was a kiddie when th
ey got in once and they had - we had the old torchlight procession with - you know, tower torches, all the way along the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Why do you think he held these views?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Liberalism? Couldn't tell you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1399755\charrsid9580092 
But I - as I said before, outside - he was - give, give, give, help to anybody. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 We could always get out of mind. See - he - he thought a lot of us somehow or the other but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 He thought you'd manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. He'd taken his shirt off and gave - he came home without a shirt, I think I told you that 
before. Mother said, what have you done with your shirt? Oh - tramp along the road never had one so I give him mine? Well you hadn't got another one. I'll get one. That was his view of life, see, he - he'd roughed it in the Army, of course they did rough 
i
t in those days. As he - as he said, in those days - men - as I told you - like beer. Well whether it's true or not what he said it, whether it's true or not I don't know but he said that - in those days when they punished them - instead of - instead of s
a
ying so many days pay stopped, like they used to us, you get fourteen days pay stopped, something like that when we were in the Army, it was - they used to pay you every day instead of weekly, a sort of punishment so he wouldn't have a lump sum. But it - 
they - they done a petty crime they'd get that's days pay to get - beer. That's funny wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you think that your father thought that the working man had a square deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. No, he was - of course Socialism and Labour party wasn't about 
then, it was only Liberal and - I - I think today - I think today that he'd have been a Communist. I think today he would have been a Communist. There was no yes sir about my father. Not my - nor my - my - my second - my brother next to me higher who had 
his jaw blown away he - he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 Communist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 worse than Russians. He said, shoot all the Royal Family, shoot all the lot of them. And he was offered - the - my father's Commanding Officer was my brother's Commanding Officer and he come down this house here - an
d said, get your son to soldier, he's a fine smart, you know, he's absolutely a soldier barring he will not have - he won't be disciplined. He don't like any - anybody above him. We've offered him - promotions, stripes and all. He don't want them, he don'
t
 want them, he don't want anybody - not with stripes - he don't believe - he couldn't - he couldn't - over other man, all men are equal he says, that fashion see, like that. That - that was my brother. That - he's - my father's Commanding Officer come dow
n here, I remember it now, that was Major Brown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your mother take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. She was - she was - she was too busy helping people - other people, otherwise she would probably -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 She didn't have any views then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. But of course women never had a vote then either did they? There made a lot of difference didn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, well it must have been before 1919, 'cos I was a boy, I was a boy at school when I joined the procession.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you know what party he voted for?
