Liberal. Oh Liberal. Yes. Oh it - 'cos him and a fellow - soldier with him, they name Rayburn lived round the next street, he was a Conservative and they used to joke but rowing like but - nasty snipes with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  another over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you know if your mother voted in 1918 when women got the vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 1918. No, my mother - 1918? No, she never voted. I'm trying to think when my mother died, she died in April - I know 
the date she died, April the fifteenth. And I was trying to think and I think my mother - when you - you asked me about her - about her age didn't you. I think she was fifty-seven or something like that. Somewhere round about fifty-seven when she died. Sh
e - no, she died of cancer. No, she never voted then, did they get the vote in - 1918, did they. No, I don't think she voted. I'm certain she never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job or their house if they voted dif
