'd take out - anything to get out of the house I mean. If he was alive now - I'd - in the same position and of the same mind as me - as - as he was, say I was the same mind as my father now and I - I'm doing that job to get a bit of money. That's all, dow
n
 there in and cash out. And this - we had this repolished here now and that bought - 'cos our firm give me twenty pounds see, cheque. Well I said to her, well this want's doing, gal, we'll spend it trying to do this, make it a little bit better. My father
,
 if he got his drink and he'd pawn that off and get something for his - for - a hundredth of what it's worth see, or sell this, could bring somebody down here. If I was my father. That is - and had his drinking habits and all that silly ways, see - that's
 
