oor and - somebody down there'd call, she'd go down there and - nothing for it see, nothing for it. But if she went to the house of course, like with a maternity case of course she used to get paid naturally enough, she would do. And she'd get so - much l
i
ke for sitting up with people when they died and laid them out. All that. Well when she was dying - the lady lived up in Bisburn Road, I don't know if she's still alive now, I remember her now, my mother was as yellow as that like - terrible. Oh, I was up
