\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, like boot clubs, sick clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. As I told you befo
re, don't you remember, I said how lucky I was to be able - to be able to bury her because a chap at our place, we were so slack at work at that time and he went - and his father was an insurance agent, well he went - he started - his father started him u
p with an insurance }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 book,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 gave some of his book to him, and he asked all us chaps to come in who worked the like to give a start off and I put my mother in for sixpence a week. See. Well - how lucky I was because - in one way - well you say now, I'm not luc
ky losing her but - just one year and one week I was paid in that. See, if you'd have paid it under a year you don't get the full benefit, I got the full benefit out and the undertaker never took the money for ages and ages after, I could in every week af
ter week trying to pay him 'cos I had it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 
But - if - old Bill Mostyn hadn't have left our place to went - to go in the insurance agent - of course we was on short time than, I used to walk right to Reading Bridge and back every morning and - I used to never had a - ha'penny. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 'Course my - my sister next to me then well she stopped at home to look after the - me mother, she never went to work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 
There was only my money coming in the house, 'cos me brother wasn't old enough to go to work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So - I was - and I - we 
was on - what was it, twenty-two - twenty something like that, hours a week it was. I used to walk to Reading Bridge and when - when - I was remembering when Easter time come - come - got a nice - ten days holiday - no pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 This would be disaster wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 It was disaster. I think I was in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes, we was all - all right. My sister - my sister next door, she's died since - she was just like my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was she the one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Yes. More than any one of them I think. Yes, she was good. 'Course me other - of course she got - they was all three married then, the eldest one was married, she was married. She had a wonderful husband they were happy. And th
e eldest one, he was married, he had - five - five children, four boys and a girl and he got killed in the first world war. He was wounded five times before, they sent him out to get killed. And the other one, he was married. See. And me sister was marrie
d, so of course I was the eldest to look after them, all like that, see. 'Cos me mother and these two you see. And you couldn't go and get stuff like you can now, you couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 As a child who did you play with, brothers, sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 W
ell never had much time to play, I mean, if I did any of that because I used to my life was - after say I was twelve, working, milk round doing things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did you play when you did play, was it in the yard, garden, street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Streets it'd be. Of course - we got the park -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever play in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 other peoples}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. The only - I - I said last week, the only time I - only time we ever we went in other peoples houses was when we went to }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Langsholme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  Street to read the c
omics on a Saturday night. That was my mother's friend she was, that was the woman, they used to take us up there, she had a night off one Saturday night when we would play. I'd read the comics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What games did you play when you did used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
What before - like before - you're talking about before like 1910 aren't you? Now then - I used to - the only game I played like see was have a kick about the play - on the doings - I never - played nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well if you got dirty you had a good hiding. Especially if me father saw it. He was brutal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well they were - my others were and all that you see but - the other ones -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no. Oh no, no, no, there was nothing - there was nothing of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Only the I.O.G.T. see, that was - that was - Independent Order o
f Good Templars you see, you never had - no - nothing to do with drink or anything like that. And I never drank not before I went in the Army. And I were I would never drink - drink to excess if I got drinking and I never have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you spend your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well I didn't have any free - I mean - I mean - to remember like much - before hadn't, you - you can't, not, I never had no - no hobbies or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go fishing or for walks or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Never owned a bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You didn't go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you collect anything, keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Never had any pets. My father had this rabbits once, I told you that before didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 But you didn't have any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
No. Oh my - my brother - who's older next to me up he had a - I remember him having a cat when we lived up the top of the road and what recalled that to my kind that is because at that time the mail - the Royal Mail - used to come from Oxford wi
th horse - horse driven, straight through from Oxford to Reading and through there. It'd come through at eight o'clock at night and ten o'clock at night. You could tell the time by them. See. And - the cat - the driver of a van ran over and killed my brot
h
er's cat, it was only horse and - horse and - horse man like see driven then. They killed my brother's cat. Well then he - he waited for the driver the next night and - wanted to kill him. That was - that's when the horse driven vans like, the Mail van th
at was, the mail van. Used to come through here at eight o'clock at night and ten o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Oh well, I said before, I - I didn't have any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go to theatres, concerts and music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Not - not whilst I was at school no. No. Well there wasn't many about then was there now cinemas like there are now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 I - the - the boss I worked for, I - I'll tell you the truth, I say I never went anywhere because the boss I worked for, Mr Price, 
he took us to see - oh - what was it how - it was a - it wasn't pictures like you have nowadays, it was - oh dear oh dear, what did they call it - yes, more - more of slides and all that but it was at Town Hall, I know, it was jolly good whatever it was t
o me anyway, because it was something new. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh dear oh dear. It wasn't - like we know pictures. Oh dear oh dear, I don't know what it was new. It - it was - we had a magic lanterns and all that, they had - they had it - they had a magic lantern over the scho
ol. All that sort of fashion. We had that at school. And talking about that guv'nor of mine who - who I worked for then. I - I did have - they allowed me - six weeks off from school when I was there because he was took ill and I done the whole milk round 
o
n my own and he - of course he paid me extra and all that for that business and they give me time of from school, that was when I was at school. And he took me done - talk about clothes again, 'cos I told before on there. In the market place they used to 
have a - every Saturday they used to have a sale - like they do nowadays, they used to have a secondhand shop there. He took me down there and bought me a - overcoat - I never had one. After he got better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Might get a penny or tuppence or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, not - no regular pocket money, oh dear, dear, dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 If you got any at all what would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I suppose a licorice stick or something like that. You 
get them for a farthing. Licorice strip. I can't remember anything else. We never used to have a lot, that was it - we was poverty stricken our lot, our house was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, no. Only my - I told you before, my aunt - her sister in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} used to send us - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Nothing else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. They was in a different station to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 She - she never - until she took ill that time I never known her ill. Oh she wouldn't say she was if she was see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters sere born, who looked after you and how you managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh me brother and me granny - we had granny - she was there - she kept on - I don't - I couldn't tell when she died but we was all born.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So you'd no difficulty then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No - only - 
I don't know who he was - his name was Jim Rush, that's what I think, I - I told you before, there was some place at - Map - Maple Durham because my - used to call him Uncle Jim, Jim Rush and he - he - drowned himself in Maple Durham Lock. That's the only
 one I can remember. And he used to come in to Reading every Friday, now - you've put something in my head now. Because he used to come into {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Reading{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 every - before I was on the milk round and that, and then meet him down in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Caversham Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and he would b
uy some lardy cake for us. Yes. And he - he - and he had a - only had one leg I think if I remember right, because when he - he went - he jumped in the Caversham lock with his stick and drowned himself in the lock. Always remember that. That was you know.
 That was - 'cos we used to have in them - in them old days they used to have memorials like a - used to have them framed, anybody died the old undertakers used to get ready themselves. Well we'd have two or three of them in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Friends? Oh-oh, not half - bags of friends, you call them friends, I mean, my mother's was true friends but our father's was-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well my - father sees in the - in the pubs. Of course my mother'
s - see, they come and see her here like. This is - is honest, you could - doctors are still alive now, they - they - they - when my mother was ill - doctors came down to see my mother. Not - not a - not in the profession. But as friends you see. Because 
she had her own doctor, but they came down as well. So you can tell she was a good lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And your father, did friends come to see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh he - he - he used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 bring}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  'em. Me - now the thing you see, that was what I'm saying - you - you shouldn't have to say it about - but I mean - if he bought anybody home - he expected them to be fed but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 hadn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  bought nothing in. You see what I mean. It's my mother - it's my mother you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no, they never - I mean, 
no, it was - my mother never - I mean they was - it was - there was never - never the togetherness that you find nowadays between them. You - you - do you know what I mean, now, there's never that, oh no, no, no. They was - husband and wife. She had her c
hildren, bring them up, that was it and all about it sort of business see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I can't - I would never say - invited like, there is a couple, we used to have people come - drop in but I mean invited wasn't thi
s. I can't remember that, no. They did - if anybody come my mother was one, if she was home she'd always welcome them and that and everything like that but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 They tended to call in casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 That's right. Well the - the - all the ladies like she'd been nursing and that, yes, they'd come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the neighbours come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
What, come indoors? Oh - only next door they would be like that, see, nothing - not - 'course there wasn't all these people about then in them - you wouldn't get these, see,
 as I say, when we were brought up there - there was only those few houses up the top and these two or four houses we came in 'em, the first tenants and all these came afterwards, I mean it was - I mean - Reading is - is a city now, it was a village you m
ight say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I - I - can never remember my father and mother ever going out together. No. No, can never remember them going out together. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Many people divide society into diffe
rent social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Before 1918? Oh yes, I - I - I always thought there was an upper class and lower class sort of thing, you know, that's wh
at I always - always thought that. Well I think there still is now -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 But you were aware of it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Oh certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Which class would you say you belonged to yourselves in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh - working class. That's only just - I know 
- I'm not going to say a lower class because we tried to keep ourselves up, we - I mean - there was one thing as taught me, my young life, with my parents - that I - my wife - I never make her work - do this, that, do that, I'll always do - I'm not trying
 
to swank or make myself look big - but it's made me a different man from what I should have been perhaps if they'd been - if my father and mother had been different. My - I wanted to do - do - like my mother. Yes. And - you can ask her, there she's there 
and I'll - I - I wouldn't - no. But we was - when we was on short time she wanted to go to work. I said, no. I'd have left, I wouldn't have a slave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What sort of people belonged to the same class as you would you say, what sort of occupations did they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I could - I mean - I - just the same as me, that's all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 When you were young I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh when I was younger? Well they'd be all - work - the people like you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 The ones that you thought were in the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh well, they was all in the same class who lived round about us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What sort of people belonged to the other class, the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well they - they just be - they be farmers or something like that I suppose, or shop owners, they just that little bit -
 because you can't say there's - 'cos the other people'd be living in the Bath Road and all that sort of thing you see. Because I always - I always say that when I hear somebody grumbling or somebody swanking I say, I - I just turn round and openly - turn
 round and say, you might as well live in the Bath Road, you don't want to live down here. You see, your place is in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bath Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. See - what they - when these people show airs to me I - I - I've got that - I say - I've got - if you don't want me, you're too big, go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no. No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 
You mustn't - they wouldn't - I don't think if the parents'd do - make you do that - don't know what my dad felt about it he wouldn't tie you to it, you went your own way.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 To who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You had to - everybody. Everybody. Yes, he was - my father was dead on th
at too, funny thing isn't it, but - he wouldn't. If he thought somebody was trying to - bigger than him he'd tell them so but he - you had to do, to everybody. Respect your elders and everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was there anyone you called sir or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Sir - you called your - well I mean - the schoolmaster sir. Or any - well you could - you speak to any man you call him sir in the street.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you call anyone master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Madam, yes. Not master. I - I always think now I don't - I can't say what I thought then but I always think my -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. I mean, they always called my mother like sort of nurse. Anybody - any of friends come round to her called her nurse. That wa
s always - not like - I've been in hospital, you call them nurse but always like nurse. Because of the children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 In the district who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I - in - well I should say your M.P. was. Like - your M.P's I
 think were. I can't see that - nobody else. Oh - like Huntley and Palmers I think, I mean - I think every - I think every boss in those days were - a youngster and that was always frightened of their guv'nor, say their gov'nor was the best guv'nor there 
w
as in - when they worked there. But you had to treat them with respect because of that. I mean, you treated - I mean, at school you treated your teachers with respect, see what I mean. But otherwise I - I don't think there's like - like today any of these
 glamorous - glamorous people about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh, bar - I can remember one doctor who everybody thought great respect of, that was - he lived at the corner of Howard Street because he would walk to his patients and my mother's told
 us that she's seen to some places where he's been to and - like - poor people. He said, you don't want me. This is what you want. He give 'em a ticket to go to Bayliss's at the corner of West Street used to be there - food. Ah but that - and he was - oh 
what was his name, he - it was a sort of a foreign name, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Japanese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 or some of that. But he never had - of course in them days they used to ride around in horse and carriage, see. He'd walk. Money to his patients. It's not medicine you want. Food. So - that w
as - he - he was at the Corner of Howard Street, Oxford Road. And - is name's gone from my memory for a minute. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What about shopkeepers, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well, they always spoke to - same as it is now near enough I suppose only o
f course - there was more shopkeepers in those days then today, the shops are - done by workers aren't they, by big concerns, like see there's only ordinary people in there, like us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh they were - they were all right, yes. They used to give you the stick and all that but they was good. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 But you used to look up to them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes, I think you look up and respected your teachers. In point of fact they made you, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Who do you think the teachers associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well amongst theirselves, I think. Of course they were - they were - I mean, there - there's a difference in class, in one way there - there's a sort of a class distinction. If you met them in the street, see, you call them sir. But if you m
et your next door neighbour in the street you say Mr so and so. But, I mean, the man next door worked for his living, that's - that's all they was doing but in them days - well you - well in fact we still do it. Although I - I go round there, I call them 
all Mr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And clergy, who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, I can't - I can't see that, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Farmers yes, well farmers is all right, there's old - Midgen was the farmer down here them, lived up in the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bunker Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, got the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Tylers{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, 
his cottage is pulled down. He was quite all right, to you, you could up there and - like say when you were a youngster you - he'd sell you milk straight from the cow cheap sometimes. He was all right, not so bad. Let you go on his field back. I went roun
d his field as long as you never went on the field, see. Yes. He was very - young - youngsters you got there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well my employers was a - he was a good man, what I - I mean when I was at school, he was good to me sort of thing. Well I t
old you he fed me well and other - and when I went to work my employer was also a good man. He was - he wasn't one of those who wanted - ten hours of you for eight. He was good he was. Yes. But I - I think on the whole the employers take it all in, I was 
lucky I think now with the employer I think I was. Even though she was saying something, he was outside see for those - labour. Hard job was those - they wanted to live - live in the houses they bought so they could turn you out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What sort of people wo
uld you say went to the church in those days and the chapel, was there any sort of social difference between the sort of people who went to church and went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well with the chapel, well, they - I don't think they associated very much. But my 
opinion - they were all darned hypocrites. That's what I'm thinking now. What I think now. I - I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 But did you see any difference in the social classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. Oh they - they - they talked to one another jobs the same but I mean it wasn't
 as if they was - went two parties or two different countries, wouldn't associate like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 The same sort of class as people went to church as to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Oh yes. Would be. But - the thing was there - Conservative see, church. Liberals chapel. I
 remember that, oh yes, the Baptist, there was two different - in the political line. You - you cold bet your last - shilling on the - it was Tories if you went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where you lived did all the people in the lower class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh well - well there wasn't - there wasn't all that difference in it, there was some - of course, I mean, as happened like my father he wasn't no tradesman, well there was just up the top must a b
it past here there was a - a man was a blacksmith. Another father was a - a train driver this way along there, well of course - they got - better money than labourer would, see, they could - their - their children, now you was introduced to one of those t
hey would have a better life than I had. You see what I mean I mean. If you worked on - although a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 railway man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 never got a lot of money, nobody - money wasn't big in those days, but I mean, there was just that little bit. And I mean - a shilling or two then was like say ten shillings or two now. Made a lot of difference.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no, there was - I don't think there was much of that, not in the working class, not - not - don't matter where 
you worked, unless - the - you get it the same now, I should say, if you worked in an office you were better than the man who - worked down - on the - on the floor. 'Cos the office staff - wear a collar and tie and you were a suit of overalls. There's jus
t that bit of difference. That's now and I think it was the same then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. There was that, oh yes, there was some rough and some respectable. Certainly there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes, because - in - that - that still exists today. If you're a - but not so much if you - one you leave a firm. If you're a fitter's mate in those days you were a fitter's mate, 
see, and you was classed as - you had to get that there - well the same thing happens today. It's worse today in one way, on one way I mean because - at the firm I work for, say I had to do a job and I - assembling a thing and wanted a bit of paint put on
 
there before I put it together, it got to be painted, well I get a paint pot and put it on. But you can't do that nowadays, you've got to wait 'til that - a painter comes along to do it. Which in my idea is silly. Time wasted. But in those - in the old da
y
s you never had that, that way, but - you - you'd - call yourself, well, like we - I was - I was in the end a tradesmen but - my mate, he would be my mate, if I said, you've got to do that - you've got to do that sort of fashion. But he couldn't tell me w
hat to do. That was in the - that was in the younger days and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You didn't feel any sort of social distinction though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no, no inferior - no, what do they call it - inferiority complexions. No, no, no. Oh no, you were all good chums sort of fashion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well - I - I think my - my mother in one respect everybody but - my father I said before was - the big noises, no. See. And that come out again in my seco
nd brother. Whereas my eldest brother was - he was different altogether again. He was - don't matter who you was, you were - you were one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. No. No. No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well I - well I - it must have done somehow or other because - because - although when I remember it. I hardly - must be because my mother's sister - she was right up, my mot
her's - one of my mother's sisters married a match manufacturer see. If you don't mention his name - he was - they go back in records, R Banner Company of - they sold - they sold out in the end to - to Bryant and - Mays. Because that was the - that was - 
m
y Uncle Charlie, he used to send me like cigarettes and he invited me to their house during the war you see. Well then - they had servants and all the lot. See. Then - my other mother's sister she married a - an actor and they were on - both on the same k
ind of ladder. And my - my cousins from that family of Bells, the match manufacturer, Bromley-by-Bow, they went - they went to - a couple of them went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for education. So there was a - somehow - as I told you before my granny - what there was I do 
not know, it was kept from us, but my granny used to say - I - I told you before, I told you not to marry him, you married for that uniform. See. He was a smart man. Smart, very smart, but - she married somebody lower then - she was perhaps. Well very hig
h mother was the way she - I don't know where her - where }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 she}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  was born I don't. That was all kept secret }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  all of us. But I do know about them because they was - it's a come of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember anyone being described as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 real}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
No. Not - not to say - oh, I'll say one and I'll tell you two or three of them, you've got it down there. My mother. But that'll be - that's nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You said she was described as this because everybody had such respect for her, for her character and work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember seeing a policeman around here as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. One - we used to have one policeman down and he lived the bottom of - in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Upshore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} bottom of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Beecham Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And I can recall that they said that
 when he retired he - he'd taken one case and one case - one case in all his career, one case only. And that - and - the case he had was - was - I mustn't mention the name of course but they - but they was - oh - what do they call the people who catch peo
p
le stuff - like - like rabbits and all that. Poachers, Poachers, all that. Well they had dogs and they could call this dog and it would go away. They taught it to go away, come to them you see, so they never caught them on that games. But they caught them
 
once when they went over the railway banks over here down the path some. And - they - they done a train. They stole bacon and all that off the train as the trains were waiting and they buried it in the back garden just round the back of the how do you do 
t
here. And Stibby Gold was the name of the policeman, Stibby - everybody knew Stibby Gold 'cos he was only policeman there down here, and he - that was the police station, it's next to that - Banks Post Office on Oxford Road, it's a fish shop now I think i
t is. Anyway it was his house, and they told Stibby Gold to arrest him. As - arrest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 Rushy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 Bate. And - and this - man, I knew him well, knew the - the family of them. He said, Stibby, he went to his house see, he said, Stibby, if you let me go in the Albion,
 he said, and have a couple of pints before he, he said, I'll come quietly. If you says I can't go - you won't take me. But - he - but he told Stibby - he says, Stibby let him go in and have his couple of drinks and took him up there, and they reckon that
's the only arrest Stibby ever made. He was - he was like one of the people all around, mind you there was no - yes, that was the only body he arrested. And his son went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Birmingham{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} police force. Well they're next door, that's him now. A
nd he was there all the time, never altered. Lived there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh everybody liked Stibby Gold, they all - everybody - he was a chap - well, one arrest in his life. And told to arrest the man, he was a great man, he - he co
ol 'em all down, Stibby, he'd come along and cool a man down - which is better than hollering and shouting at that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your mother ever say to you I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh no. She only had to say, I'll tell your father. That was - you know -
 that was good enough for us. It wouldn't do for - him to tell her - here to tell him that we was bad, oh dear, oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Policeman. He treated them with respect, he was great - he had control, t
hey did what - Stib - they always called him Stibby Gold. Stibby Gold say, now come on, come on. Hadn't you better get home? They'd go home. You see, he was that kind, it was better that - barking at them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Rented, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Not the landlord, no, the - they had agents then like they do now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Perriss}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  was the - we see Mr , he was - and our first landlord when I was a child like you know, school age and that. He was a good man, he was,
 honestly. He wasn't a - one of these men who - get you throw out because - else we should have been thrown out. When - with my father, because - we should have been thrown out because we owed a lot of rent sometimes. Waiting for pension day. He was a goo
d - Perris was a good landlord. Well - he was an agent, for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Dunlop\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  around here see, the coal merchants.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends met?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 One long struggle. Yes, it was, I did at any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember what you thought about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Thought? Well I've thought about it since but not - not so much then I don't suppose because I didn't know so much I said before I thought - it got in my mind when I got older that it's made a different man of me
, my own opinion at any rate I tried it. I said my wife would never go to work and I - if she went to work I'd walk out. That's honest true that. That's - I mean I might have been different if - they'd been different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What difference did it make to the family when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh well, it was terrible for us in one way I mean - I mean we was all sort of not clothed properly. We couldn't be - on these secondhand - dad's old - of course mother again would get help certain places whe
re she'd been to, they give her and all that. You see, she'd had a lot of stuff give her. They was kind - everybody was kind to her, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Your father was very frequently out of work wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. Well we - to tell the truth I can't remember any - sort of job he was in work for a long time honestly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever get help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No, no. No, nothing like that one. The only time see as I remember was like when they applied when I - I was t
old by my paymaster like, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 - to - I was - I gave as - as much as I could to help my dad and he had to ask for a little extra and that's what he do, and he told me to write to her and I did write to her and that's the answer she got. What I told you before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You never got anything from parish relief or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
No. No, we had no parish relief, no. No. There wasn't much parish relief about them days was there as I know, I can't remember anyway, I can't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You never had any help from the Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
No. I can't - well I can't remember 'em doing anything like that. Now you mention - I've heard of them, Board of Guardians and parish relief and all that but - I think my mother's mother was too proud to have anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well - the only - my mother and father would make us respect everybody and all that but - lessons on school or anything like that, no, but when my father was at the V.S.A. he bought me 
a sixpenny medal as I told you before and I had to play and we sing hymns on a Sunday night. Stop in, hymns. But there - after that session went - back to the old game again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Four I think we started at then. Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 When you first started school what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Nine. Nine - about nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And when did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I think - I think it's near enough the same time now, half past four or something like that, if I remember rightly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You went fell time did you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 School - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Afternoon as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What kind of school was it, a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 A board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What they call it - that's educational like isn't it, like - a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did they call it a board school in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Boarding school was one that paid to go to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was it a council school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Council school, yes, run by the - corporation like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. All a mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 About a minute. They all went all round here like see. There was never - there was never anybody being paid to go to scho
ol, I mean like paying - have to pay a tram fare or anything like that because they weren't far enough away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. By ourselves, just trot across the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Ooh - well they treated us - they always treated us very well I think, I think the teachers was great.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, I did, I - liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh they was good, they was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Good manners, tidiness, yes, certainly they did, they did to that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, that was another thing, you had the stick if you wasn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. They treat everybody lovely they did. You had to learn that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And the ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. That's why I say like the sir business that's - I mean - or Miss or Madam, or the only thing you do was at scho
ol. Outside - unless it was a clergyman or anyone like that, yes sir and all that. If you went to a shop it'd be - you knew him it'd be Mr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well the cane - we used to get caned.
 If - if a teacher just - for what we done we get caned. Yes. There wasn't very much - there wasn't so much of the - the stopping in after school to - lessons or anything like that. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the girls get caned a well as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I couldn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092  tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 you about that. I - no, I don't think they did. Might have got caned more after I was - twelve than ever I did before when I went on the milk round and that was at - I could - I - honestly I told then and there, I - I hope he died a terrible death, I 
didn't like that schoolmaster at the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 When you moved from this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 To Wilson school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What sort of things would you get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh playing about or anything like that out of fashion or - or I suppose if you was insolent but 
of course you weren't allowed to be insolent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes, my - father did all like that, he - like sort of let you down yet - when I left - when I - when I finished up at fourteen I could have we
nt to Reading school or I was going to the - Bluecoat part, but he said, work. See, so I had to work, see, and that's why - that's why I thought the headmaster - I had to go to Wilson school and I was on the milk round, and being on the milk round sometim
e
s I got there late and the had me once in front of the whole assembly of the Wilson Boy - senior department, out there having this - they call's 'em sessions here, we used to call them prayers, and he - I walked in late. He said Rush. I think - oh, terrib
l
e the way he said it. Late again. We don't want boys like you here in our school. Because I wasn't stopping 'til I was sixteen you see, because my father said I - he wouldn't sign to say - I'm - I was leaving at fourteen, had to stop see. And he'd - I cam
e
 on his part because he wanted boys to sixteen I know, but I couldn't help it. See, so I had to go out there and I fainted away at that school. He caned me in front of all the - all the school. I dropped down on - in the - in that big hall. He had a littl
e
 place down there, like the one there. He used to say, you go to my room and await my coming. Then you knew what you had then. I mean it was - that was - you - I never had no respect for the man. Yet he was a - I think up here he was wonderful. Came up th
e
re. But I couldn't help my father not saying I had to leave school at fourteen. I couldn't help going to work and being late. If I was late I run, but I was late. Then he said I - we don't want boys like you at our school - because I couldn't stop 'til I 
was sixteen see. Which was - he was right but then she shouldn't accept them. Unless he had to I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did your parents visit the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, they never - not like they do now, there was none of these - I can't - oh well
 I can't remember them - I - I can't remember it, if there was I can't remember it. Not like there is now, there's open days up there now this week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the other children at school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. Mostly the same. Some of them like was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 tradesmen\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  daughters, I mean, like craftsmen at work - children I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. I think we were all treated the same. Bar up there, like I mean, that was terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, I can't remember there was, I mean, there was - I mean you was too close to one another, you was more of a families I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. I went to Wilson. When I was - I went up there when I was - well about between eleven and twelve or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What time did you start then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 That's the same - same time - they was all the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What kind of a school was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well it's - I was at - see, that was - I don't know what they call it - it's like - it's like a secondary modern now they call it. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Wilson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  Senor they called it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh that's not far you see, I - just the same walked - just walked it, it's just past the barracks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How long did this take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh - I suppose ten minutes to get to school easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did you have your midday meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 At home. Unless - unless I was - when I got in the dairy you see, I worked at the dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What did you think of that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Not much. I mean - I mean, I - I was - I was - in - I was - in my opinion - my own whic
h could be either against, in my opinion I was caned for something that I didn't do of my own accord and it hurt me - and it stuck into me ever since. That were - and it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 hurts}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  to think that that was done to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 The punishments there were canings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. Was the cane, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the teachers there emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners, tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes, that was taught there really. Yes, punctuality was a great thing, punctuality. Which is a great thing to teach you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was this a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, mixed school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. Oh some of 'em was like - of you'll take similar to mine some of them had little shops like there would be.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You didn't go on to another school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, no. No, I had to leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Fourteen when I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh would you have done, yes. I did have the opportunity see, but my father said no. I - I said I had to leave at fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go to evening classes or anything after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I do - now - now, yes, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 regret}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  that I wasn't allowed to 
stop on. And I also regret - I might be like my father in a way, my daughter Pam. If my wife had told me beforehand I knew - she went to - Kendrick, and she wanted to stop on. I'd - I'd always held her close to me, frightened she was going to do - and she
 
went there and it come to me that Pam was passing good results everything lovely, was going lovely. And then I used to say, Pam, what do you want to go in for? What are you doing? And the answer I always got, I don't know. Every term I asked her again. So
 
I sat down with the wife one day, I said, daughter I said, we've got to do something, I said. She's content to stop at that school forever in her life. It's our fault, I said, we've - kept her so close to us that she's frightened to step out into life. So
, I said, we've got to make her step out into life, I says, she'll be like it all her life. So - all right. So I said, Pam -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. I mean, I reckon - I mean education in my opinion - if anything I 
go - I should have liked to have been there a lot more. I should have liked to have stopped, like she did. I think it's one of the finest things out, education. I - I tried to tell - I tried to tell all the children that come knocking can - from Kendrick 
-
 not Kendrick - from Wilson, when they come along here to dinner, when they was young - stop - are you leaving school this ...? Yes. Stop on, I should, have a - you stop on, I keep telling them. Because I know an education is a benefit. Don't you think so
? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I told you that, you've got that haven't you? Oh yes, I - I went - on the milk round. On the milk round working for - and all that
. And mornings and times at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get this job, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh I just - I expect - I think heard he wanted somebody, I went and got it, went and asked him for it, it's just how it come along, I can't remember now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh I did - first I had to deliver milk. Then we had to - had to clean out his horses. At dinnertime - and have a wash then clean the cans, have me dinner and then go back to school. Then at night time, as in the morning we de
livered the milk of course. Get there at half past five in the morning. And then at night used to go and do the same thing. Clean out horses, help with the harness clean the cans, wash, have me tea there. Oh and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 W
ell half past - I used to get there at half past five in the morning, finish near nine o'clock as we could like see, yes, I had to get to school. But I used to have me breakfast in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And then dinner hour you'd go back for about half an hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I - I'd go back there, I had half hour for dinner then, had all me dinner in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 And how long would you spend there in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes to about seven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So that would be about three hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. That's including me - they give me tea see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So that would be about seven hours a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Cleanliness. He would have cleanliness and time keeping again see, the people must have their milk. He looked after his animals well and all his utensils had to be spotlessly 
clean always, which is a fine thing, clean shoes, he had boots to go out and all that you see. Well that - you get two years of that - drummed into you, that left - last you for the rest of your life, see, then go into the Army it's again in there but - i
t started off there, it made it, my Army life easier. Comes natural.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you work the same hours Sunday and Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No, Saturday - Sundays we - only one round Sundays. All weekdays twice. And Saturdays sometimes a bit later because we were co
llecting the money and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So what time did you start on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, same time get up in the morning, or six o'clock, didn't matter - not so much because the workmen's not going to work, so early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You did about seven hours a day didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Something like that it would be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Would it be less on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. We - we knocked off at dinnertime. Because those times included me stopping having my meals with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. When did holidays with pay come out? Not so many years ago did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I think I had half a crown a week. And meals, yes. Which was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you feel it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. 'Cos he was good - I had - they had go
od food. Good food. Good food - and plenty of it. There was always - they never - skimped you or nothing like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You had breakfast, lunch and tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Lunch and tea, yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 All of it. Yes. Yes. She gave me - about - I had tuppence or threepence back something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What was it spent on, the money you gave your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I don't know, on the home, oh the home, yes. And that helped to keep us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh there was only - he had a - two daughters and a son, there's - the daughter was the eldest one - the other two was a lot younger see, going to school. They was all going to school. There was nobody e
lse, only the - boss like say and his wife. There one man business. He had three ponies. And that's where I think now he taught me something which I see beforehand that you don't see now was the love of animals, he'd - like I mean the old horse trams they
 used to look after their horses well and treat 'em well, and so did he, he thought the world of his horses - his ponies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Oh he treated us good - he was all right, good as gold. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
He never - he was no slave driver, 
I mean, when - we had to get the - of the customers certainly to make - get before he went to work, I mean everybody went to work earlier than they do nowadays. See, so you had to be up in the morning for their cup of tea. The milkman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
I didn't like going dinnertimes I must say that. I wanted to stop in the play ground. I - I did stop in the playground to be honest and got chucked off - told off them as you might say, for being late but - I mean it's natural sometimes you rebel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. I don't think it could do very well. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you do any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I went in the smithing trade, blacksmiths mate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Do you remember how you got this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I think somebody told me the job was going so I went and got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 As a - help the blacksmith. Use a sledgehammer, twelve pound.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
That was - there we started at seven. Seven up 'til twelve I think it was. And one up 'til five. Or up to half past five I can't remember which. Then - seven o'clock I think it was 'til twe
lve on a Saturday. He used to - well - in now - in those days you see, when I went after that, I went to where I am - where I left - I left there and went to where I am, we used to put in fifty-three hours a week. That's a - a full time job you see. That 
was the time everybody worked then near enough. Most of them worked fifty-four. Yes, but we worked fifty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You didn't work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. Oh no. Or if you did have to work that was all overtime see. That was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Saturday was your half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. And the other place I went to see, we used to start at six o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. There was not much - how long ago is it we had holidays with pay? It's not long been has it? Mind, if you - unless you was in the
 office staff see that's where they - they were the lucky people because they was paid - fortnightly annually or something like that they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Can you remember what you were paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 When I first started? I think I got twelve shillings a week, then, I think that's what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Well it was then - for a boy. Because after that I left and I went to - I was - I was only there - I think it was six months or something like that and I went to - where I am - where I left. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you give any of the money to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well I give all - she give back see. She give me - I don't know whether it were a shilling or two shillings I had back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What was the money you gave her spend on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well that was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 How did you get on with the people you worked with there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
All right. The one I worked with was a - was a tradesman of the highest quality. He got me - afterwards he got me - the job where I was - when I - I've had all me life, you se
e, but he got me the job there. And he - he taught me the trade - he was a highly qualified man. He was a - oh well - anyway, afterwards when I went to the other firm this same man, there was a job going at Huntley and Palmers as a matter of fact, funny t
h
ing to say that isn't it, and he; said to me, George - you go there and the job is yours. We used to work at six o'clock in the - go there and get there at six o'clock in the morning for there. We worked from six up 'til - half past eight. Half past eight
 
to nine, breakfast time. Nine, I think it was, to twelve. And one to five. And - we used to work to six o'clock on the Friday night and knock off at twelve Saturday. And if you work that out that comes to fifty-three hours I think. And - if you take a - l
i
ke labourers pay for that fifty-three hours or if you worked fifty-four hours - he would get eighteen shillings a week. He would - if he worked the fifty-four. If he worked the fifty-three, well he'd get seventeen and - about eighteen and eight - no, nine
t
een and eightpence see. As - as they paid then for labourers in this town there. Well this man told me, he said, George, they wants a smith I know at the factory, he said. Huntley and Palmers. I've worked there. He told me the man's name, Mr Blackwell in 
c
harge. Mention my name, he says, tell him I recommended you, he said, you'll get the job. Well the only thing about - was wrong with this man, I've told you about - of course you see I expect she's got fed up with hearing it - he was like my father, drunk
a
rd. He could - he said - he could lose half hour, see, he'd lose half hour, come in at half past six. Pubs opened as I told you before, six o'clock - near where I worked was the Rising Sun public house. Jimmy had to go and have his drink before he come do
w
n. To get a bit more he had another one, he wouldn't come in while eight - you could lose what they call before breakfast. That was like from six - you start nine instead of - nine o'clock, you lost two and a half hours work. And if - if Jimmy lost his tw
o
 and a half hours he tried to keep going as long as he could perhaps 'til nine o'clock and this that and - have the day, see. Well he - he told me this - cut the story a bit short, he told me go up there. So I had to tell a lie to our foreman. Who was the
n
 - he was a cockney. I said, I can remember the words to this day, I said - our Jimmy says, you'll get off here, he don't get there before half past nine, it's no good ageing down there before or nine or half past, he said, because he - one of the big ogy
s like. However, so I told the foreman, I said, Arthur, I said, I got the - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 jaws}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 ache, I says, I says, I think I'll go and have the tooth out. And I remember him his old cockney way, he said, that's right }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 George}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 , he said, you go and have him out, he said. He said, don't stick that pain, he said, I've had enough of it myself. O.K. - lovely. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 
Off I goes, I goes up to apartments. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I contacts this gentleman. O.K. So I said to him I said, I've got the - I said, Mr Jimmy Pullen, I said, who I work with now - tol
d me that he recommended me, to mention his name. He said, ooh - the words he said, what a tradesman. What a wonderful man he said. If he recommended you, he said, you're good enough for us, he said. If he'd only leave the drink alone, that's the words he
 
used, yes. Just hang on, he said, a minute will you? So I said, yes sir, I sat down. He went in another room. Well I guessed then what he was going to do. Get through to our firm. Because he asked me where I worked. Of course when I got back - and all tha
t
 - to work - the foreman come up and he called me everything, and he had to that 'course - in them days - well like it is now, Employers' Federation, can't employ you unless you left and all that, well I never had the job, else I should have been - I migh
t have been at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 Huntley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
 and Palmers working see, and that's - but he - he - when he told you to do a job, talk about teaching you to do a job, and it went well in my stead by being a good - him being a good tradesman. Never let a job beat you. Never lose you
r temper with a job, 'cos you can lose your temper if it's going wrong can't you. You - I mean you can do this that and the other, well it won't go right you see - well - he'd say, now come on, it's your turn, get on and make this. See, me do it, make it 
a
nd all that. I'd get on and do one, two then - then something go wrong, and I'd - might swear or do something like that. Wallop. Cuff me from here to there, he was only a little bloke. But he stuck me see, and that's how I learnt me trade because I was lu
cky enough to have a good tradesman teaching me, taught me what to do. In respect of work, and he was good. And that's how I've come to work - and I - I stopped there - all me life. Well, barring the war. Which has happened.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes
. I - I - because I - I think that is - that's a case of anybody else, I think if you could master anything you must like it mustn't you, else you - else you never master it, would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I always
 - the first - I - I went back to me same firm gain you see, well I - I carried on as I done - oh any sort of job beside smithing, like engineering or smithing. I done plating, like marking out jobs, getting them all ready, all that. Make riveting. Well t
hey never give me a job I couldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you a fitter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I don't - no, I was - I was engineering smith see but I could fit and they also - I also was left in charge very often of the job, oh yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You stayed in the one place all your life after your apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
I stayed one - yes. Yes, yes, yes, - well, the old guv'nor was a - see they had - they only had two guv'nors that is all the time I was there, one and he died and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Would you have preferred another type of occupation than the one you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What thinking over - backwards }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 like.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  Well al - all as I say is I - I - I wouldn't have minded - I liked it, yes, certainly, but - I wish I'd had the sense to have more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9308085\charrsid9580092 imitative}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  to push myself forward, to say - instead of saying, 
I'm satisfied, give the - say I'm not going to do it. Loyalty - now to me - you can be too loyal. If you want - if - if it's cash you're after because - cash you can't - you can't live without it. But therefore loyalty - ought to come second sometimes in 
my opinion. I - I think I was - let's say I was to loyal, I - I should have pushed - I let other people push in front of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You did serve an apprenticeship didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I did do but I - I -
 I - got out of it when - because - I didn't believe in one thing they done once see. There was - in my - that's was my own opinion, see. My own opinion they served a man wrong, I said, if that's the union I've finished with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you take part in any of its activities when you were in the union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
No. I'm on none of the committees. And since the - and since I was out of the union, when they had a - when they had a one day strike, I - I went out with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you feel that the employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
All - all the - now, in our firm, our old employer had a great interest in our - us. In the workmen and all, I think - he was philanthropic sort of outside the way he played it and I think he'd - if he'd h
ave lived he'd have treated us all better than we was treated, I mean, this - this who are now is much - is like a firm, moneymaking man see. He likes to make money but I think he would have - he was more humane. He thought of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Not - not so much divided, I can't see that - not - not divided, I mean there's bound to be one or two little - rows or something like that, but not a - a great division at all, not - n
ot - not - no, no, no. You might have it - one now and again, I mean it's not - I mean over here as you can't - you've to leave that haven't you really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you feel that or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 Oh - there was sometimes, I mean - there's like - like - it\rquote s like - I was going to say to our daughter and her doctor I think. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I'm the blacksmith, you're my mate, you stop like that, you do as your told, finish, I
'm not going to show you nothing see, unless you go through it like me see. There - there is still that opinion about. I - I heard it - I heard it at our place - I want more money if he - have I got to show him? I want more money. Well that's - that's one
 of the things that happens isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Full time work? What - what way do you mean? Oh no, I was happy, I liked full time work. I liked it better than - better tha
n half time working, dear oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 After you left school did you continue to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes. I lived at home all me life. Well, barring the Army of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You still felt the same towards your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 What about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes, oh I can't see any difference, I can't remember any difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 I me
an, if you take it - you take it, see - from when I left school, see at fourteen years to when I was sixteen, that war came along quick didn't it. See, that war did a lot didn't it, and we weren't long together, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you spend your Sunday any differently once you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I never went to - I never went to Sunday school. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 So you gave it all up once you'd started to work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 All that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Yes, I did a bit. But - not excessive. Just - when - anything was on that was all, not - not all the way through see, just at an election was on and all that I think I'd take it up. I was Liberal then, like me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You were a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Why did you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Because me dad did, that was all I expect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Was the general election before 1919, did you vote then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Before 1919? No. No. We did - we never had the vote then did we. No, it was twenty-one wasn't it you 
had to have the vote then didn't you. No, I was - I mean, 1919 - was twenty - when I joined the Army. '14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever work for one of the parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 No. I never took part in anything of those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, you didn't have much spare time when you were at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Not - not at school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things once you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh I started playing football and all that. I played football team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 In a way it was only the spare time you had?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes. Oh yes, after I started work, after - yes, I played football, yes, straight away. So that must - I - I know that because I played like for the - the only team }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 if}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  they had I would - I think, until this - in this war, that was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 full}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  side of j
uniors. I played before the war for them see, that was before, that was - you can tell when it was, it was when the - the - the - my first year like you say of competitive football was when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 Lusitania}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  went down, and I think that was - I was about eighteen or just under then. Junior football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Once you'd started full time work you'd more spare time than you'd had at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh certainly, I - oh yes, I played football then and I played - I played for - for another team I played for Allen Park Hal
l, we used to go out training and all, run about and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you go out in the evenings when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Oh yes. We went out - you see, I could go anywhere then, sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Well I sometimes used to go up - what was it - the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 tuppence}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  clubs up the other end of town, penny fringe, up the - up at the factory. There was a - a - a cinematograph sort of fashion there was up there. I think up there used to get a cup of tea and a }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092  - and a - a cup of tea for - go in for a penny or something like that,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Who did you used to go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Boys. My old pals or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16731435\charrsid9580092 I made - and - one of them is still alive now, name is Pals, but I got to now more because like playing football you knew them then. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Buy to go out with, I met two like - more - different - and I didn't - that I didn't know at all before and we went out together at nights and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Where did you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Through football. Through football, see. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7745245 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 Did you ever bring friends home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4540718 GR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5376311\charrsid9580092 
Oh yes, one of them - my - like I call one I went to school with and all, Billy Bridgman, he could walk into this house and I could walk into his house. Just as were in f
amily. That was Billy Bridgman, see that was of the - he - and - he was in the war - the first world war see and we met after the first world war more - world war - they met pals, made new pals in there like, see one was in the - was in Berkshire I.S.A. o
r
 two of 'em was, and I was in - I was in the - I joined the regular R.E's, see, about - for the duration of war, I came with the regulars. Well when we came home again see, they'd met - their pals'd had come home, they come home all right, I mean, a sort 
o
f a gang you'd call us of about six. That's when I started having a drink. I - we never - well the only day we drank to excess was on - Celebration Day, I know that. And we went down to Reading and we got through every public house. The Ship Hotel then, D
uke Street. And we worked out - we lost our suits of clothes - one lost his jacket, a new jacket, I lost a new raincoat and my pal lost a new raincoat.
